Section-02 5-Setting up our development enviroment

---

1. Download Nodejs latest stable verion
2. Download IDE or Code Editor like VS Code (my prefrence)

3. Download extensions in the VS Code

1) ESLint --> automatically find errors in the code
2) Prettier Code Formatter
3) One Monokai Theme (Color Theme)
4) Material Icon Theme (Icon Theme)

4. Setting in VS Code

1) Auto Save Setting -> onFocusChange
2) Default format -> Prettier Code Formatter
3) Format on Save
4) ESllint run - ontype or onsave

Let's now to finish , let's just set up some snippets.
Snippets are basically some piece of predefined code that we can use to greatly speed up Development
